<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n42023c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42023c">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42023c"> 23(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> versicle</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A little more attention to the translation of the 3rd and 6th verses of chapter xiii. of Leviticus by the Septuagint would have prevented the former <font color="green">[Catholics]</font> from falling into their sacrilegious errors, and would have saved the latter <font color="green">[Protestants]</font> from wasting so much time in refuting errors which refute themselves. <small> Chiniquy, <a name="CPWC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CPWC"><cite title="source">The Priest The Woman and The Confessional</cite></a> (n.d.) 110</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
